Author::::<a href="http://social.ndtv.com/groups.php?id=658161" target="_blank">Mohan</a>

Comment::::<div class="com_user_text">
                            The 3 famous Padayatras of independent India are:- The Young Turk Chandra Shekhar as president of Janata Dal undertook a marathon walk (known as Bharat Yatra) from Kanyakumari in South India to Raj Ghat in New Delhi covering a total distance of 4260 kilometers from January 6, 1983 to June 25, 1983. The main aim was to highlight the problems of the rural areas and eliminate the social inequalities and disparities prevalent. Dr. Y S Rajashekar Reddy walked under the blistering sun across the Andhra state and brought the Congress government back into power in 2004. He walked 1475 kilometers covering 640 villages for 68 days in the scorching hot sun and reached closer to the hearts of people and understanding the needs of the lesser privileged. But after getting power the biggest scams of independent India like Jalayagnam had its origin during his tenure. Treading the Gandhian Path, environmentalist Sunderlal Bahuguna marched from Kashmir to Kohima in 1982-83. The first to join the padayatra was 72 year old Gandhian activist, Sri Ratanchand Dehloo. The 4870 km trans Himalayan march was completed in 300 days. The Yatra carried the message of the vital importance of forests for our survival
